{"title": "Library Essays; Papers Related to the Work of Public Libraries", "description": "This 1920 collection of essays gathers together 25 years of papers, articles, and presentations given by Arthur E. Bostwick. The ideas in many of the essays still hold true today: he advocates for such things as an expanded mission of the public library, professionalism in librarianship, and the keeping of statistics. The essays cover such topics as \u201cThe Library as the Educational Center of the Town,\u201d \u201cThe Future of Library Work,\u201d and \u201cThree Kinds of Librarians.\u201d Spoiler alert, Bostwick believes that the third kind of librarian, the \u201clibrarian of to-day,\u201d should be proactive in offering materials wanted by their patrons, should work to spread library services to excluded populations, and should be \u201calways looking for trouble.\u201d  Bostwick was a Yale-educated librarian who during his career headed up the New York Public Library and the St. Louis Public Library. He was the president of the American Library Association 1907-1908. - Summary by Verla Viera", "duration": 48615, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12983", "name": "Arthur Elmore Bostwick"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/libraryessays_2403_librivox/libraryessays_2403.jpg", "copyright_year": "1920", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Verla Viera"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Christine Rottger"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Christine Rottger"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/libraryessays_2403_librivox/libraryessays_00_bostwick_64kb.mp3", "duration": 68}, {"section": 1, "title": "Pains and Penalties in Library Work", "readers": [16619], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/libraryessays_2403_librivox/libraryessays_01_bostwick_64kb.mp3", "duration":